---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions" description="Solarelites Terms and Conditions – governing the use of our services and website." noIndex={true}>
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-display font-800 text-5xl tracking-tight mb-4" style="letter-spacing: -0.03em;">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-sm mb-12" style="color: var(--muted-foreground);">Last updated: January 1, 2025</p>

      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>By accessing or using Solarelites' services and website, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree, please do not use our services.</p>

        <h2>2. Services</h2>
        <p>Solarelites provides solar energy installation, consultation, maintenance, and government subsidy assistance services. Specific terms for each service are outlined in individual service agreements.</p>

        <h2>3. Quotations and Pricing</h2>
        <p>All quotations provided are valid for 30 days unless otherwise stated. Prices are subject to change based on material costs, site conditions, and government policy changes. Final pricing is confirmed in the signed service agreement.</p>

        <h2>4. Government Subsidy Assistance</h2>
        <p>Solarelites provides assistance with government subsidy applications as a service to our customers. Subsidy approval is subject to government policies and DISCOM approvals, which are beyond our control. We do not guarantee subsidy disbursement but commit to following all correct procedures.</p>

        <h2>5. Warranties</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Solar Panels:</strong> 25-year performance warranty (manufacturer)</li>
          <li><strong>Inverters:</strong> 5–10 year warranty (manufacturer)</li>
          <li><strong>Workmanship:</strong> 10-year warranty (Solarelites)</li>
          <li><strong>Structural:</strong> 10-year warranty on mounting structures</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Warranties are void in cases of damage due to acts of God, misuse, or unauthorised modifications.</p>

        <h2>6. Payment Terms</h2>
        <p>Standard payment structure: 30% advance, 60% before installation, 10% on commissioning. EMI and solar loan options are available subject to financier approval.</p>

        <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>Solarelites' liability is limited to the value of the contracted services. We are not liable for indirect losses including loss of profits, business interruption, or grid-related issues beyond our control.</p>

        <h2>8. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These terms are governed by the laws of India. Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of courts in Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra.</p>

        <h2>9. Contact</h2>
        <p>For queries about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@solarelites.in">info@solarelites.in</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
